    <div class="col-md-7 order-md-1">
      <h4>How to quick start a meeting?</h4>
      <h5>This website allows you to set up meetings quickly without signing up or logging in, to do so</h5>
      <li class="help-list">1. Click on Host Meet</li>
      <li class="help-list">2. Fill your name that will be shared with others</li>
      <li class="help-list">3. Check if you want others to see your video or hear you</li>
      <li class="help-list">4. Copy the Meet Id and share it with the people you want to have the meeting.</li>
      <br>
      <h5>If you have a MeetId that is created with the Host Meet option then</h5>
      <li class="help-list">1. Click on Join Meet</li>
      <li class="help-list">2. Fill your name and the Id you have</li>
      <li class="help-list">3. Check if you want others to see your video or hear you</li>
      <li class="help-list">4. Clicking on Join Meet you will be redirected to the meeting…Easy Peasy</li>
      <br><br>
      <p><em>If you are being constantly redirected to the Join Meet page, its possible you have a MeetId that was created in a group. You cannot join meets of a group from this page. To do that you have to sign up, ask for the group key and join
          that
          group and from the group dashboard you have to join the meet.
        </em></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5 order-md-2">
      <img class="bd-placeholder-img bd-placeholder-img-lg featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto" width="500" height="500" src="/images/hostmeet.png" aria-label="Placeholder: 500x500">
